<br>
I learned about you from John on the FAOL BB.  I have BS in Forestry (Wildlife Management Major) and pretty new to flyfishing.  I would like a better understanding of stream biology and fishery mangement to go with my new found passion.<br>
<br>
Do you know of some good sources of information on these subjects?  I used to buy books from Patrica Ledlie, a biology/conservation bookseller.  These books were aimed at biologists, foresters, students and similar people.  I believe the company was sold or went out of business.  Any advice will be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Mike <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rickgolden@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Rick Golden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Environment Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(1/29/03 9:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> fishery management</span><hr size=1> Mike, <br>
Good to see a forester interested in these issues!  A great book on general stream ecology is &quot;the ecology of running waters&quot; by H.B.N Hynes, published by the Liverpool University Press, 1970 (ISBN#0 85323 100 1).  It may be out of print, and, if so, check with powells.com, the online used book store.  If they do not have it in stock, you can have them notify you when it comes in.  I will also reply to you tomorrow with some journal article references on stream geomorphology (the physical shape and behavior of streams) and stream ecology.  Thanks for your interest!  -- Rick  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fishtx@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>FishTX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(1/30/03 10:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fishery management</span><hr size=1> Rick<br>
